An Asynchronous WebSocket Client Library for Scala

     val w: Websocket = new Websocket();

     w.open(getTargetUrl).listener(new MessageListener() {
        def onMessage(message: String) {
            // Do something
        }
     }).send("Hello World");

You can also add message Serializer and Deserializer and typed listener

     w.open(getTargetUrl)
       .listener(new MessageListener[MyMessage]() {
          def onMessage(message: MyMessage) {
                // MyMessage Object
           }
         })
       .deserializer(new MyMessageDeserializer())
       .send("Hello World");



